The National Board for Technical Education (NBTE) has approved six new additional courses for the Federal Polytechnic, Ado-Ekiti, Ekiti State. The director of information in the polytechnic, Mr. Ade Adeyemi-Adejolu, in a statement said the newly approved courses would begin from the 2019/2020 academic session. He listed the new courses to include National Diploma in Mass Communication, Arts and Industrial Design, and Horticultural Technology and Taxation. NDLEA arrests policeman, trafficker, for supplying drugs to Boko Haram insurgents in Borno Nigeria needs resourceful youths for national development ―… One year after, Lagos brings back Ready Set Work programme Rivers, Ogun, Enugu top 2019 Lafarge  national literacy… What I would love to achieve with my tenure — SSANIP… Others are Higher National Diploma (HND) in Ceramics Technology; Crop Production Technology and HND programme in Purchasing and Supply. “The commencement of the six new programmes stemmed from the recent approval by the NBTE following the resource visitation conducted earlier this year. “Also, other existing academic programmes that successfully scaled through the accreditation/reaccreditation visitation process are National Diploma in Agricultural Technology, among others.” Office Technology and Management, as well as Higher National Diploma programme in Office Technology and Management.  Nigerian Tribune SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
